<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>${app_title}</title>
    <link data-trunk rel="copy-dir" href="assets" />
    <!-- The wasm is compiled with `+atomics,+bulk-memory` (see .cargo/config.toml)
         plus rustc's default wasm features (sign-ext, nontrapping-float-to-int, ...),
         so in `--release` Trunk's bundled wasm-opt aborts validation ("Atomic
         operations require threads [--enable-threads]", then "all used features
         should be allowed") unless told those features are on. `--all-features`
         allows every feature so validation matches whatever rustc emitted;
         `data-wasm-opt-params` (release-only) forwards it to wasm-opt. -->
    <link data-trunk rel="rust" href="../../Cargo.toml" data-wasm-opt="z"
          data-wasm-opt-params="--all-features" />
  </head>
  <style>
    #aimer_app {
         position: absolute;
         top: 0;
         left: 0;
         width: 100vw;
         height: 100vh;
         outline: none;
     }
  </style>
  <body>
    <div id="aimer_app"></div>
  </body>
</html>
